{"id": "unknown-2026-04-27-001", "date": "2026-04-27", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Mon"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": ["growth", "pressure"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "Vietnam’s economy maintains strong momentum amid uncertainties: AMRO", "content": "Vietnam’s economy has demonstrated notable resilience despite continuing global uncertainties, as per AMRO \nAfter an exceptionally strong 2025 growth performance, its growth is expected to soften to around 7.2 per cent in 2026-27. \nSafeguarding macro-financial stability will require a prudent, well-calibrated policy mix that avoids procyclicality, while managing emerging macro‑financial pressures. ", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/vietnam-s-economy-maintains-strong-momentum-amid-uncertainties-amro-309917-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-04-27-002", "date": "2026-04-27", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Mon"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "negative", "score": -0.5, "keywords": ["[否定]growth"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "Adverse impact of Iran war may hit India largely in Q1 FY27: ICRA", "content": "The YoY growth in India’s economic activity, as measured by the ICRA business activity monitor, eased to a five-month low of 7.6 per cent in March this year from 10 per cent in February 2026.\nICRA pegs India’s GDP growth at 7 per cent in Q4 FY26.\nA large part of the adverse impact of the Middle East crisis is likely to manifest in Q1 FY27. ", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/adverse-impact-of-iran-war-may-hit-india-largely-in-q1-fy27-icra-309920-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-04-27-003", "date": "2026-04-27", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Mon"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": []}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "India’s polyester raw materials rise on firm feedstock trends", "content": "Polyester feedstock prices strengthened, driven by steady gains in PTA across India and China.\nCrude oil-linked cost support remained firm amid ongoing Middle East tensions, sustaining upstream momentum.\nHowever, MEG trends were mixed, reflecting uneven cost dynamics within the value chain.\nDespite this, cautious downstream demand is keeping the market largely range-bound with a mild positive bias.", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/india-s-polyester-raw-materials-rise-on-firm-feedstock-trends-309931-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-04-27-004", "date": "2026-04-27", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Mon"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": []}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "India-New Zealand FTA to boost textile exports: CITI", "content": "India’s textile and apparel exports are set to gain from the India–New Zealand FTA, which ensures duty-free access and supports market diversification.\nNew Zealand imported Indian made-up textiles worth NZ $80.22 million in 2025.\nThe pact is expected to drive value-added exports and aid India’s $350 billion sector target by 2030.", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/india-new-zealand-fta-to-boost-textile-exports-citi-309930-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-04-27-005", "date": "2026-04-27", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Mon"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "neutral", "score": 0.0, "keywords": []}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "India, New Zealand to sign FTA today", "content": "India and New Zealand will sign an FTA today that will remove tariffs on all of the former’s exports to the latter, and either sharply reduce or remove tariffs on 95 per cent of imports from the latter.\nTalks began in March 2025, after a hiatus of ten years.\nIndia feels the FTA will open new export opportunities for traditional and MSME-driven sectors, particularly in leather, handloom and handicrafts.", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/india-new-zealand-to-sign-fta-today-309929-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
{"id": "unknown-2026-04-27-006", "date": "2026-04-27", "time_tags": {"year": 2026, "quarter": "Q2", "month": 4, "week": 18, "weekday": "Mon"}, "entities": {"companies": [], "customers": [], "suppliers": []}, "topics": ["supply_chain_shift"], "sentiment": {"label": "negative", "score": -0.67, "keywords": ["decline", "slow", "weak"]}, "importance": {"score": 0.5, "reasons": []}, "title": "Bangladesh home textile exports fall 47% in Q1", "content": "Bangladesh’s home textile exports fell 47.8 per cent YoY to $170.52 million in Q1 2026, reflecting sharp demand slowdown across major markets.\nUS imports dropped 44 per cent but remained the largest destination.\nThe decline highlights inventory correction, cautious sourcing, and weakening demand across the US and Europe despite stable annual export trends.", "sources": [{"name": "fibre2fashion_textile", "url": "https://www.fibre2fashion.com/news/textile-news/bangladesh-home-textile-exports-fall-47-in-q1-309916-newsdetails.htm", "type": "rss"}]}
